\int_{A}\bigg(\int_B f(x,y)dy\bigg)dx =\int_{B}\bigg(\int_A f(x,y)dx\bigg)dy =\int_{A\times B}f(x,y)d(x,y)
\mathcal{S}(\mathbb{R}^{n}\times\mathbb{R}^{n}) \subset L^{1}(\mathbb{R}^n \times \mathbb{R}^n)
g(x,\xi) = \frac{1}{(2\pi)^{n/2}} f(x) \varphi(\xi) e^{-\xi \cdot x}.
